# Executive Summary

A malicious PowerShell download cradle attack was detected involving the execution of encoded and obfuscated PowerShell commands designed to retrieve remote payloads from external URLs.

The attack was identified through PowerShell Script Block Logging and Sysmon process creation events collected within the Elastic Stack SIEM environment. Detection rules successfully identified suspicious use of `Net.WebClient`, `IEX`, and Base64-encoded PowerShell execution.

